name: Build and test

on:
  push:
    branches: [ main ]
  pull_request:
    branches: [ main ]

jobs:
  lint:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    strategy:
      matrix:
        python-version: [ '3.9' ]
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v2
      - name: Set up Python ${{ matrix.python-version }}
        uses: actions/setup-python@v2
        with:
          python-version: ${{ matrix.python-version }}
      - name: Install dependencies
        run: |
          pip install flake8 flake8-black flake8-isort
      - name: Check code quality
        run: |
          flake8 --ignore=F401,E203 src/ test/

  test:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    strategy:
      matrix:
        python-version: [ '3.9' ]

    steps:

      #----------------------------------------------
      #       check-out repo and set-up python
      #----------------------------------------------
      - name: Check out repository
        uses: actions/checkout@v3

      - name: Set up Python ${{ matrix.python-version }}
        uses: actions/setup-python@v3
        with:
          python-version: ${{ matrix.python-version }}

      #----------------------------------------------
      #          install & configure poetry
      #----------------------------------------------
      - name: Install Poetry
        uses: snok/install-poetry@v1.3
        with:
          virtualenvs-create: true
          virtualenvs-in-project: true

      #----------------------------------------------
      #       load cached venv if cache exists
      #----------------------------------------------
      - name: Load cached venv
        id: cached-poetry-dependencies
        uses: actions/cache@v3
        with:
          path: .venv
          key: venv-${{ runner.os }}-${{ hashFiles('**/poetry.lock') }}

      #----------------------------------------------
      # install dependencies if cache does not exist
      #----------------------------------------------
      - name: Install dependencies
        if: steps.cached-poetry-dependencies.outputs.cache-hit != 'true'
        run: poetry install --no-interaction --no-root

      #----------------------------------------------
      #              run test suite
      #----------------------------------------------
      - name: Run tests
        run: poetry run pytest

+"""Repro script for default enrichment_property_list=None bug.
@@ -1,0 +3,49 @@
+This script patches the network-dependent SPARQL querying layer to return
+deterministic results, then exercises Query.simple_enrichment().
+
+Expected (current buggy behavior): TypeError due to joining None property_list.
+"""
+
+from unittest.mock import patch
+
+from pandasaurus.query import Query
+
+
+def fake_run_sparql_query(query: str):
+    # Minimal behavior to support CurieValidator + enrichment calls.
+    if "rdf:type owl:Class" in query:
+        # get_label_query
+        return iter(
+            [
+                {"term": "CL:0000084", "label": "T cell"},
+                {"term": "CL:0000236", "label": "B cell"},
+            ]
+        )
+    if "owl:deprecated" in query:
+        # get_replaced_by_query
+        return iter([])
+    if "GRAPH <http://reasoner.renci.org/redundant>" in query:
+        return iter(
+            [
+                {
+                    "s": "CL:0000084",
+                    "s_label": "T cell",
+                    "p": "rdfs:subClassOf",
+                    "o": "CL:0000236",
+                    "o_label": "B cell",
+                }
+            ]
+        )
+    return iter([])
+
+
+def main():
+    with patch("pandasaurus.utils.query_utils.run_sparql_query", side_effect=fake_run_sparql_query):
+        q = Query(["CL:0000084", "CL:0000236"])  # no enrichment_property_list passed
+        df = q.simple_enrichment()
+        print(df)
+
+
+if __name__ == "__main__":
+    main()
